title: For Sale:   Walther 9mm P38 variant P1 Lightweight Military P-1 German Federal Border Guard BGS P-38 Descendant CA OK with 1 Factory 8 Shot Magazine
postcontent:
Our # HGP1U

Photos are representative, but buyer will receive a pistol in very similar condition and from the same lot. At press time on this ad, we had a few 1963 and 1964 production P1s that are C&R Eligible. All these are good to go on the California Roster until Feb 2015. Dealers, collectors, and law enforcement may take any number of very similar Walthers at the same per-pistol price and with no extra shipping charges. From duty on the front lines of the Cold War with the Federal German Border Police, Bundesgrenzschutz, or BGS, here is a very attractive Cold War piece manufactured in the Federal Republic of Germany, West Germany, in the 1960s and 1970s. This pistol is certainly a symbolic piece of the Berlin Wall, and the island of Democracy that West Germany stood for. Each specimen bears correct West German proof marks, and their only U.S. marking is the federally mandated import stamp, PW Arms, so marked on the right forward side of the slide. Slide and frame have matching numbers. This is a lightweight, alloy-frame model P-1 in 9mm Luger, production of which began in 1963. It is very similar to, and a direct descendant of, the fabled steel frame P38 of World War II. Construction is durable anodized alloy frame with matte military finish on its barrel , slide, and all its steel parts. Type is traditional double and single action semi-auto with full safety / decocking lever. The P-1 has a firing pin safety as well, but no magazine safety. Magazine holds 8 rounds of 9mm Luger, Parabellum, 9x19 ammunition, call it what you will, THE 9mm. Barrel is 4 7/8 inches. Sights are dovetailed notch rear and blade front. Weight empty is 28.2 ounces. Surface detractions are minimal, only faint amounts of whitening on its sharp edges and light holster contact streaking. We rate these pistols as Very Good, close to Excellent, 85 to 90 percent vicinity by our estimate. If refinished, the lettering is so sharp it doesn’t matter. Photos, at any rate, should suffice for our distinguished shoppers to check our grading. Bore, chamber, and mechanism are all bright, clean, and excellent, and the West German Police always took good care of their firearms anyway. These are excellent quality pistols, but not designed for +P loads. Its historical importance includes the fact that the P38 was the direct ancestor to our own well known 3900 and 5900 Smith & Wessons, and the Beretta 92 / M9. Own one of these Cold Warrior Walther P-1 pistol, the one in the photos or one of its substantially identical mates, for only $ 339.00. California DOJ Roster Status good until Feb 2015.
